---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/about.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="About · Sudhanshu Kashyap"
      description="About Sudhanshu Kashyap — software engineer, open source contributor, and occasional Genshin resin spender."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main class="about-main">

      <h1>About</h1>

      <p>
        Hey, I'm Sudhanshu. I'm a software engineer at JP Morgan Chase, where I spend my time
        building backend systems and data platforms — and lately wiring up LLM agents to automate
        the parts of engineering that nobody enjoys.
      </p>
      <p>
        I studied Computer Science at BITS Pilani and joined JPMC shortly after graduating in 2022.
        In the summer of 2023 I got to contribute to FreeBSD through Google Summer of Code, which
        was one of the better decisions I've made — good codebase, good mentors, genuinely learned
        a lot.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of work I maintain a few open source projects, most notably
        <a href="https://github.com/mightyjoe781/bootbaker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BootBaker</a>,
        a tool for managing bootable OS environments that started as a personal itch and turned into
        something other people actually use.
      </p>

      <h2>Timeline</h2>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-entry">
          <span class="timeline-date">Jul 2022 – Present</span>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <strong>Software Engineer — JP Morgan Chase</strong>
            <p>Backend systems, data engineering, and LLM tooling</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-entry">
          <span class="timeline-date">May – Sep 2023</span>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <strong>GSoC Contributor — FreeBSD Foundation</strong>
            <p>Port infrastructure and tooling under Google Summer of Code.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-entry">
          <span class="timeline-date">2018 – 2022</span>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <strong>B.E. Computer Science — BITS Pilani</strong>
            <p>GPA 8.85/10. Where I picked up systems thinking and way too many side projects.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Outside the terminal</h2>
      <p>
        I'm a big fan of open-world games with real craft behind them. Alan Wake 2 was something
        else — story, atmosphere, the whole thing. Genshin Impact has its hooks in me despite my
        best efforts. The backlog keeps growing faster than I can clear it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Linux has been my daily driver for years and I enjoy the rabbit holes it leads into —
        kernel configs, custom distros, self-hosting whatever I can. There's something satisfying
        about owning the stack end to end.
      </p>
      <p>
        I play guitar, mostly self-taught and mostly learning by ear. Music is a big part of how
        I decompress. I also read — slower than I'd like, but consistently.
      </p>

      <section class="about-contact">
        <h2>Say hi</h2>
        <p>
          I'm most reachable at
          <a href="mailto:sudhanshu@sudomoon.com">sudhanshu@sudomoon.com</a> or on
          <a href="https://github.com/mightyjoe781" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
          If you're building something interesting or just want to talk shop, I'm usually up for it.
        </p>
      </section>

    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
